{
  "video_id": "EFkE_beKk-w",
  "title": "Solar Cheaper Than Coal By 2021",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 688.0,
      "end_time": 3863.0,
      "text": "- By 2021, solar is gonna\nbe cheaper than coal,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 3863.0,
      "end_time": 8030.0,
      "text": "a new report from Bloomberg\nNew Energy Finance suggests."
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 14920.0,
      "end_time": 16515.0,
      "text": "The new report shows\nthat the price of solar"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 16515.0,
      "end_time": 18241.0,
      "text": "is dropping rapidly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 18241.0,
      "end_time": 21031.0,
      "text": "much faster than originally anticipated."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 21031.0,
      "end_time": 23200.0,
      "text": "The lead author, Seb Henbest, said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 23200.0,
      "end_time": 25443.0,
      "text": "\"Costs of new energy\ntechnologies are falling"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 25443.0,
      "end_time": 29278.0,
      "text": "\"in a way that is more a\nmatter of when than if.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29278.0,
      "end_time": 31481.0,
      "text": "If their report is correct,\nthen we could see a decline"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 31481.0,
      "end_time": 36371.0,
      "text": "in global CO2 levels as early\nas 2026, which is much sooner"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 36371.0,
      "end_time": 39656.0,
      "text": "than the International\nEnergy Agency forecast."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 39656.0,
      "end_time": 41097.0,
      "text": "China and India are the biggest markets"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 41097.0,
      "end_time": 44498.0,
      "text": "for these new solar farms\nand account for $4 trillion"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44498.0,
      "end_time": 49436.0,
      "text": "of investment, which is about\n39% of the overall industry."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 49436.0,
      "end_time": 51840.0,
      "text": "Now, these two countries\nare still spinning up"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 51840.0,
      "end_time": 56172.0,
      "text": "coal plants really fast, but I\nthink once the price of solar"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 56172.0,
      "end_time": 60184.0,
      "text": "gets below where it is for\nthe other types of energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 60184.0,
      "end_time": 63310.0,
      "text": "we're gonna see a big\nshift really quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 63310.0,
      "end_time": 68166.0,
      "text": "In fact, China aims to spend\nat least 360 billion with a B"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 68166.0,
      "end_time": 72339.0,
      "text": "on renewable energy by 2020\nto fight climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 72339.0,
      "end_time": 74174.0,
      "text": "This is of course to help them deal"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 74174.0,
      "end_time": 76391.0,
      "text": "with the severe pollution in their cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 76391.0,
      "end_time": 80290.0,
      "text": "Now, China is also\nincentivizing their consumers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 80290.0,
      "end_time": 82562.0,
      "text": "their citizens, to buy electric vehicles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 82562.0,
      "end_time": 84172.0,
      "text": "and in fact last year they had"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 84172.0,
      "end_time": 87517.0,
      "text": "over 350,000 electric vehicles sold,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 87517.0,
      "end_time": 89973.0,
      "text": "which is far and away the most"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 89973.0,
      "end_time": 91867.0,
      "text": "out of any country in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 91867.0,
      "end_time": 94238.0,
      "text": "In one way, you could say\nthat they're the world leaders"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 94238.0,
      "end_time": 97178.0,
      "text": "in shifting us into more\nrenewable forms of energy"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 97178.0,
      "end_time": 100691.0,
      "text": "and forms of transportation\nsuch as electric vehicles."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 100691.0,
      "end_time": 102720.0,
      "text": "In the US, besides Donald Trump saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 102720.0,
      "end_time": 104604.0,
      "text": "\"We're gonna bring back the coal industry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 104604.0,
      "end_time": 105938.0,
      "text": "\"save the coal industry,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 105938.0,
      "end_time": 109147.0,
      "text": "we're gonna see prices for\nsolar continue to drop."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 109147.0,
      "end_time": 111194.0,
      "text": "The report predicts that in the US,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 111194.0,
      "end_time": 115361.0,
      "text": "solar costs will drop by 67%\nin 2040 and 63% in Canada."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117787.0,
      "end_time": 119592.0,
      "text": "That's huge but still\ndoesn't hold a candle"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 119592.0,
      "end_time": 123005.0,
      "text": "to the 85% price drop predicted in Japan."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 123005.0,
      "end_time": 127286.0,
      "text": "In fact, they're looking at\na 70% price drop by 2022."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 127286.0,
      "end_time": 129246.0,
      "text": "That's only five years from now."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 129246.00000000001,
      "end_time": 131612.0,
      "text": "Now, I have to pause here\nfor a second and talk"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 131612.0,
      "end_time": 135061.0,
      "text": "a little bit about why I\nfocus on the price so much."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 135061.0,
      "end_time": 137942.0,
      "text": "You see, in the US, we've\npoliticized the argument"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 137942.0,
      "end_time": 140403.0,
      "text": "over climate change, whereas\nmost of the rest of the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 140403.0,
      "end_time": 142974.0,
      "text": "really doesn't see it\nas an argument anymore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 142974.0,
      "end_time": 146042.0,
      "text": "as more a fact and something\nthat we need to act upon."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 146042.0,
      "end_time": 148329.0,
      "text": "That's why literally\nevery country in the world"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148329.0,
      "end_time": 150846.0,
      "text": "signed onto the Paris Accord."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 150846.0,
      "end_time": 153360.0,
      "text": "So, when you have something\nthat is objectively"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 153360.0,
      "end_time": 156497.0,
      "text": "cheaper and better in every way,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 156497.0,
      "end_time": 159028.0,
      "text": "no one is gonna stop this from happening."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 159028.0,
      "end_time": 160652.0,
      "text": "No one's gonna stand in the way and say,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 160652.0,
      "end_time": 163584.0,
      "text": "\"Let's pay more for the same thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 163584.0,
      "end_time": 167594.0,
      "text": "\"that we could get cheaper and\nbetter and easier over here.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 167594.0,
      "end_time": 168902.0,
      "text": "It just doesn't work that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 168902.0,
      "end_time": 171657.0,
      "text": "In fact, the reason oil\nand things like plastic"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 171657.0,
      "end_time": 174440.0,
      "text": "have been with us for\nso many centuries now"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 174440.0,
      "end_time": 177928.0,
      "text": "is because of how cheap\nand efficient they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 177928.0,
      "end_time": 181292.0,
      "text": "If we found a better\nway to do this earlier,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 181292.0,
      "end_time": 184075.0,
      "text": "then we would've already made\nthe switch, but we haven't,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 184075.0,
      "end_time": 186921.0,
      "text": "and until we started to realize the impact"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 186921.0,
      "end_time": 190026.0,
      "text": "that this industry is\nhaving on our environment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 190026.0,
      "end_time": 192581.0,
      "text": "we really didn't open\nour eyes to even looking"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 192581.0,
      "end_time": 195253.0,
      "text": "because we didn't realize\nwhy we would want that."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 195253.0,
      "end_time": 196738.0,
      "text": "Don't think for a second, though,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 196738.0,
      "end_time": 198698.0,
      "text": "that this will spell doom and gloom"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 198698.0,
      "end_time": 202876.0,
      "text": "for big oil or Opec or any of those folks."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 202876.0,
      "end_time": 205231.0,
      "text": "Companies like BP are making\ntheir first investment"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 205231.0,
      "end_time": 207656.0,
      "text": "into renewables in half a decade."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 207656.0,
      "end_time": 210301.0,
      "text": "Even Opec's top producer, Saudi Arabia,"
